The '''golden-fronted fulvetta''' ('''''Schoeniparus variegaticeps'''''), also known as the '''gold-fronted fulvetta''', is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Pellorneidae]].<ref name="iucn status 17 November 2021" /><ref name=IOC10.2>{{BioRef|IOC|version=version 10.2|family=Pellorneidae |access-date=25 July 2020}}</ref>  It is [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[China]].  Its natural [[habitat]] is subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]].  It is threatened by [[habitat loss]].

